{"lemma":"رِجْسِ","slug":"رِجْسِ","root":"ر.ج.س","root_slug":"ر-ج-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ج-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رِجْس","root":"رجس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14863","n14864","n14865"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%AC%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be dirty, to be filthy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to act shamefully, to do something shameful or disgraceful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sully, to make dirty"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover with opprobrium, to make appear shameful"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pollution, dirt"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"abomination, disgrace","examples":[{"text":"ــإِنَّمَا الْخَمْرُ وَٱلْمَيْسِرُ وَٱلْأَنْصَابُ وَٱلْأَزْلَامُ رِجْسٌ مِنْ عَمَلِ الشَّيْطَانِ فَٱجْتَنِبُوهُــ","english":"...Wine/liquor and games of chance/gambling and [sacrificing upon or offering unto] stone alters/statues and [drawing or casting] divination arrows are surely an abomination, of Satan's handiwork, so shun it..."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَجِسَ (rajisa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dirty, filthy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"shameful, abominable, unholy"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14863","headword_ar":"رِجْسٌ","root":"rjs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Uncleanness, dirt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unclean, a dirty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a filthy, thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qa*arN","text_ar":"قَذَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, Msb, K, TA: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqadaru","text_ar":"القَدَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put by mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqa*arN","text_ar":"القَذَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N qa*irN","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ قَذِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hated, for its uncleanness, dirtiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filthiness: stink,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul odour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filth that comes forth from the body of a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"En-Nakkásh says that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nijosN","text_ar":"نِجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it is said in the Bári' that sometimes they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajaAsapu waAln~ajaAsapu","text_ar":"الرَّجَاسَةُ وَالنَّجَاسَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning that they make these two words syn.: (Msb:) it is also written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajisN","text_ar":"رَجِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajasN","text_ar":"رَجَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, K:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijosN nijosN","text_ar":"رِجْسٌ نِجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajisN najisN","text_ar":"رَجِسٌ نَجِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and IDrd says, I think that they also said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajasN najasN","text_ar":"رَجَسٌ نَجَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": Pr says that when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjs","text_ar":"رجس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"njs","text_ar":"نجس"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with kesr; but when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"njs","text_ar":"نجس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjs","text_ar":"رجس"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"are with fet-h. (TA.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N rijosN","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ رِجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An unclean, a dirty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a filthy, thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~abinaA jamaAEapN rajisuwna","text_ar":"مَرَّبِنَا جَمَاعَةٌ رَجِسُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najisuwna","text_ar":"نَجِسُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company of unbelievers passed by us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar and TA.) As used in the Kur vi. 125, Mujáhid explains"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ijos","text_ar":"الرِّجْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That in which is no good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any action that is disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hated, for its uncleanness, dirtiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filthiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, A, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crime:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-El-Kelbee, A, K:) so in the Kur v. 92, and vi. 146: (Ibn-El-Kelbee:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an action that leads to punishment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, K:) as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajosN","text_ar":"رَجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ vehemence of sound, ” [see 1,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijosN","text_ar":"رِجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an action the mention whereof is evil, and highly evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) sometimes it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is unlawful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbidden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unbelief: infidelity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Jaafar, A, K:) so in the Kur xxxiii. 33. (Aboo-Jaafar.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Punishment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, T, S, A, K;) a sense which Z makes tropical, as being the recompense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijos","text_ar":"رِجْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the sense of “ sin ”], (TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, A, K:) so in the Kur x. 100: like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijozN","text_ar":"رِجْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is perhaps formed from it by the change of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Fr, S:) and sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malediction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"execration."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slight, motion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Suggestion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the devil. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","A","K","Zj","T","L","Fr","S"]},{"entry_id":"n14864","headword_ar":"رَجَسٌ","root":"rjs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijosN","text_ar":"رِجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the latter, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14865","headword_ar":"رَجِسٌ","root":"rjs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijosN","text_ar":"رِجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the latter, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}